div1.p:
Q. You remember going to your brother on the 23d of April last. - A. Yes, in the forenoon I went into the shop, I saw a brown paper parcel laying on the counter, I asked the boy in the shop what it was (
John Andrew Paas
), he said he supposed it was hat buckles, and I immediately laid it down, I felt it was heavy;
John Andrew Paas
took it up and opened it, he said it was money, I did not see the contents of the parcel; the prisoner at the bar was in the shop, I know him perfectly well, I have seen him frequently at that shop.

(The examinations of Dempsey and Browner read in court, and the affidavit of
David Coleman
).
